Sixteen suspected cultists have been taken into police custody in Niger State. They were reportedly arrested in a lodge in Lapai area during a Black Axe celebration of July 7, also dubbed 7/7). Police spokesman Wasiu Abiodun said the suspects were aged between 21 and 28. They are said to be university students and freshly graduated ones. Hemp, an axe, and a concoction of hard drugs, mong other items were reportedly recovered from them.